meaning: shake out a sack, empty a container (i -)
being in existence (often translatable by English 'to have' when referring to possessions etc.)
to sprinkle (man -); instrument for sprinkling holy water in church ceremonies, blessings, etc.
direct illumination from the sun or other source of light; to eye something, see curiously
nearly, it should be so, ‘if you like’ (may also indicate that an action etc. did not actually take place or was desired by someone)
